## Feature map by phase

### Phase 0 — Scaffold (foundation)

Status: **partial** (usable sync API; not production-hardened).

- [x] HTTP server (Hono) + listen bind (`HOST` / `PORT`)
  - [x] `GET /health` → `{ status: "ok" }`
  - [x] Env validation via Zod (`CURSOR_API_KEY`, `PORT`, `HOST`, `REPOS_ROOT`, `CURSOR_MODEL`)
  - [x] `.env.example` / setup docs in README
- [x] Sync task API
  - [x] `POST /tasks` with `prompt`, `repo`, optional `model`
  - [x] Resolve repo under `REPOS_ROOT`
  - [x] Local SDK `Agent.create` + `send` + `wait`
  - [x] Always dispose agent (`asyncDispose`)
  - [x] Distinguish startup failure (`CursorAgentError`) from run failure
  - [ ] Validate repo path exists / is a git repo before run — see Phase 1
  - [ ] Async / non-blocking task lifecycle — see Phase 2
- [~] Job scheduler
  - [x] `node-cron` registration helper (`startScheduler`)
  - [ ] Default / sample jobs registered
  - [ ] Review / triage / hygiene job implementations — see Phase 2
- [x] Agent / workflow harness docs (AGENTS.md, workflow-skills, secrets scan)
- [ ] Homelab packaging — see Phase 1
- [ ] Client authentication — see Phase 1

`Verified:` — (fill when health + task smoke succeed on the host)

