### Phase 1 — Homelab-ready (next priority)

Status: **todo**. Goal: run reliably on Umbrel/Compose over Tailscale with basic client auth and safe repo resolution.

- [ ] Docker Compose stack
  - [ ] Service definition (Node 20+, port, env)
  - [ ] Persistent volume for `REPOS_ROOT` / `repos/`
  - [ ] Document Umbrel / custom-app style usage
  - **spec:** `docker-compose.spec.md`
- [ ] Tailscale-oriented defaults and docs
  - [ ] Bind / HOST guidance for tailnet access
  - [ ] Client reachability notes (no public exposure assumed)
  - **spec:** `tailscale-homelab-docs.spec.md`
- [ ] Client authentication
  - [ ] API key (or equivalent) for callers
  - [ ] Reject unauthenticated task (and mutating) routes
  - **spec:** `client-auth.spec.md`
- [ ] Repo registration and validation
  - [ ] Ensure `{REPOS_ROOT}/{repo}` exists
  - [ ] Ensure path is a git working tree (or documented allowlist)
  - [ ] Clear 4xx errors for unknown / invalid repos
  - **spec:** `repo-validation.spec.md`

