### Phase 3 — Spec harness and pluggable runners (flagship)

Status: **todo**. Goal: qualified specs drive staged, observable, resumable pipelines; runners are swappable.

- [ ] Spec schema (machine-actionable: IDs, AC, dependencies)
  - **spec:** `spec-schema.spec.md`
- [ ] Spec editor / served environment (UI TBD)
  - **spec:** `spec-editor.spec.md`
- [ ] Stage orchestration service
  - [ ] Stages: implement → build → test → deploy → review
  - [ ] Per-stage logs, artifacts, pass/fail; resumable; tied to spec sections
  - **spec:** `stage-orchestration.spec.md`
- [ ] Runner interface (do not hard-couple to `@cursor/sdk`)
  - **spec:** `harness-runner-interface.spec.md`
- [ ] Cursor SDK runner adapter (default)
  - **spec:** `runner-cursor-sdk.spec.md`
- [ ] Hermes Agent integration (orchestration, schedule, memory/skills, delegation)
  - **spec:** `hermes-integration.spec.md`
- [ ] OpenCode runner adapter
  - **spec:** `runner-opencode.spec.md`
- [ ] Multi-tenant isolation (if multiple clients share one host)
  - **spec:** `multi-tenant-isolation.spec.md`

